I remember sucessfully changing data in Dragon Warrior soundtrack (the NSF file), and I don't remember much from it. I've also attempted DW2, but I got very bad results. The hard part is to find where the song data is actually stocked (tracing code) and then the rest is to try to change the values and see what happens.<br />Capcom's game definitely have a standard setting or something. Memblers hacked most of them to throw them together in a sinlge NES rom.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue May 22, 2007 11:42 am</p><hr />
